3. What is the use of interface in Java? Or, why do we use an interface in Java? Interfaces are used for: 

• Total Abstraction: Hiding implementation details from the user. 
• Multiple Inheritance: A class can implement multiple interfaces, which is not possible with classes. 
• Loose Coupling: It allows for flexible system architecture by separating the definition from the implementation. 

